def Minutesplot(playerlist):
    Col = {"AnthonyDavis":"Black", "CarmeloAnthony":"Red", "DerrickFavors":"Green", "JuliusRandle":"Blue", "LaMarcusAldridge":"Cyan", "AaronGordon":"Yellow", "DarioSaric":"Purple", "GiannisAntetokounmpo":"Brown", "KristapsPorzingis": "Orange", "LauriMarkkanen":"Magenta"}

#Tallying up the points
Davis_tally = sum(Davis)
Aldridge_tally = sum(Aldridge)
Anthony_tally = sum(Anthony)
Favors_tally = sum(Favors)
Randle_tally = sum(Randle)

#X-Axis (Labels)
players_label = ['Anthony Davis', 'LaMarcus Aldridge', 'Carmelo Anthony', 'Derrick Favors', 'Julius Randle']
#Converting the X-Axis into an array
players_label_arr = np.array(players_label)

#Y-Axis (Values for the labels)
tally = [Davis_tally, Aldridge_tally, Anthony_tally, Favors_tally, Randle_tally]

#Plotting the Bar
plt.bar(players_label_arr, tally)

#Labelling X and Y axes
plt.xlabel('Player Names', fontsize = 20, color='DarkBlue')
plt.ylabel('Total Points', fontsize = 20, color='DarkBlue')

#The Title
plt.title("WC Power Forward - Final Rankings", fontsize=35, color="DarkBlue", fontname="Console")

#Displaying the Bar
plt.show()
